---
name: all-prelude-module-signatures
description: Signatures of all modules in IML prelude
---

Now we'll go through the signatures of modules in IML Prelude.

{% set toplevel = prelude | selectattr("module", "equalto", "") | list -%}
{% set modules = [] -%}
{% for entry in prelude if entry.module != "" -%}
  {% if entry.module not in modules -%}
    {% if modules.append(entry.module) %}{% endif -%}
  {% endif -%}
{% endfor -%}

<top-level>
top-level (readily available, no need to quantify with module name)
{% for entry in toplevel %}
  {{ entry.signature }}{% if entry.doc %}  (*  {{ entry.doc }}  *){% endif %}
{% endfor %}
</top-level>

{% for mod in modules %}
{% set mod_entries = prelude | selectattr("module", "equalto", mod) | list -%}
<module_{{ mod }}>
Module: `{{ mod }}`
```iml
module type {{ mod }} = sig
{%- for entry in mod_entries %}
  {{ entry.signature }}
{%- endfor %}
end
```
</module_{{ mod }}>
{% endfor %}
